I think this new location is nice, clean & spacious. Every staff member I’ve interacted with has been pleasant and helpful. My concerning issue is the Staff not addressing patrons who are loudly talking on their phones or making random noises. When I’ve used the computers, I’ve witnessed people having phone conversations, eating, playing videos on their phones without a headset, singing to themselves, even an individual applying deodorant under his arms then laughing & chatting with someone through his headset. This is unacceptable. It’s too distracting when you’re trying to focus. I know a business can’t predict odd behavior from their guests but they can enforce rules that are violated. What’s the point of having security? If the policy is for the staff to not confront patrons regarding these behaviors, why can’t security intervene. Hopefully, changes can be made to create a more pleasant experience for everyone.

At long last, I had the chance to explore the much-anticipated library, and it surpassed all my expectations. Having seen numerous posts about this stunning place, I can confidently say that none of them captured its true essence. From the moment you approach, the library’s striking exterior captures your attention, with modern architecture and inviting glass facades. The spacious parking lot is often bustling, a testament to its popularity, and the surrounding area boasts a delightful array of eateries and a serene lake, perfect for leisurely walks or invigorating jogs. It’s an ideal spot for anyone looking to settle down or just pay a visit.

Stepping inside the building, I was utterly captivated. The interior design is simply magnificent, with sunlight streaming in through the expansive glass windows, creating a warm and welcoming ambiance. You can even adjust the windows yourself if you prefer to shut out the distractions while focusing on your work near them. The conference rooms add an extra layer of functionality; although they have a slight echo, they provide a perfect space for meetings and can be reserved for two hours at a time.
Every library is a godsend. Our society would crumble beneath a fascist boot without libraries
Fun and quiet place to read and study.
Beautiful new library for our community! Staff was extremely friendly and helpful. Proud to call this my local library!

Beautiful new facility. The second floor has places you can read with views of the lake, many study rooms and it's walkable to the boardwalk area. The new children's section is huge floorplan wise, but I think they need to add more interactive things for kids, as there were more way kids than things to play with. I'm hoping they bring back the play kitchen, some blocks or even add a pretend vehicle like ImaginOn has (decades ago books used to be viewed & delivered via a library truck to Derita before there was a library, that would be cool to homage). I saw there's a gated grass outdoor area in the back which would be perfect for a play / climbing structure as the weather gets better! Keeping my fingers crossed 🤞
I am so happy that I get to live very closely to this library. Beautifully and designed. I could stay there all afternoon just to chill

I only saw some of the first floor today b/c I was just picking up an item on hold but what I did see was very open and spacious with lots of sunlight. It's a very nice building and I look forward to seeing more of it when I have the time. Libraries are very important to our communities as places to study, research, socialize and relax.

Poor customer service. My daughter and I went to this location today to grab some new books. Upon checking out I was told I needed to renew my library card as it had expired. Unfortunately I left my license at home inadvertently. The librarian proceeded to tell me I would not be able to check out any books because I did not have my license. She did not ask if I had any other means of proof of my address. She then proceeds to tell me my daughter can check out books at her school if she attends CMS. My daughter does not attend CMS but even if she did why would she be denied a free resource.

I asked to escalate the situation and speak with someone else. The librarian spoke with her manager/supervisor separately. When she returned it was apparent that the manager thought the situation was as silly as I thought it was. She renewed my card and I was allowed to check out the books. Needless to say I will no longer go to this location. I typically go to the Huntersville and will revert to going to this location going forward. The librarians there are much more pleasant.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi, Satira! We are grateful for your patronage. Thank you for this kind review and for sharing photos from your experience. We observe summer hours after Memorial Day at our regional branch locations, so we will be closed on Sundays starting June 5 until the end of summer. We look forward to seeing you at the next best time that works for you and your family!

reviews_data.review_text: This library is so so. The staff upon entry are super friendly and always greet me with a smile. The only negative thing I have to say is the staff toward the front (in the middle area) are so loud it’s almost hard to study most days. You would think they would at least attempt to use inside voices considering they work in the library.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your review, Bri. We are disappointed to learn you didn't have a better experience. Library's have evolved over the years to meet the growing needs of the community and, as such, libraries are no longer "shh" zones. Some of our branch locations have quiet zones and study rooms available on a first-come, first-serve basis. Please always bring share your concerns with staff and we will try our best to accommodate your needs.

The library is in a great location and is rather beautiful. The book selection is great, especially for children and teens. They also have a great amount of comic books. If you're coming here to sit and study, it can be a hit or miss, sometimes it will be rather empty and you'll be blessed with your own table, fast internet, and a quiet library, other times you'll have to share a desk (nothing wrong with that, just means you can't spread out as much), have to deal with somewhat slow internet speeds, and a bit more background noise. The staff is friendly and it's easy to head out and buy a drink and lunch and return to finish studying or whatnot. My biggest complaints are that there are not enough work spaces and the internet does not have enough bandwidth to handle the volume of traffic they get in the afternoons.

It’s an ideal spot for anyone looking to settle down or just pay a visit.

Stepping inside the building, I was utterly captivated. The interior design is simply magnificent, with sunlight streaming in through the expansive glass windows, creating a warm and welcoming ambiance. You can even adjust the windows yourself if you prefer to shut out the distractions while focusing on your work near them. The conference rooms add an extra layer of functionality; although they have a slight echo, they provide a perfect space for meetings and can be reserved for two hours at a time.

I'm hoping they bring back the play kitchen, some blocks or even add a pretend vehicle like ImaginOn has (decades ago books used to be viewed & delivered via a library truck to Derita before there was a library, that would be cool to homage). I saw there's a gated grass outdoor area in the back which would be perfect for a play / climbing structure as the weather gets better! Keeping my fingers crossed 🤞

My daughter does not attend CMS but even if she did why would she be denied a free resource.

I asked to escalate the situation and speak with someone else. The librarian spoke with her manager/supervisor separately. Needless to say I will no longer go to this location. I typically go to the Huntersville and will revert to going to this location going forward. The librarians there are much more pleasant.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your review, Bri. We are disappointed to learn you didn't have a better experience.
